From: Jacques Nilo <jacquesnilo@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] busybox 902-Lexra-jffs2-fcntl-lock

Ignore fcntl F_SETLK errors (JFFS2 does not support file locking; the warning spams every passwd invocation)

---
--- a/libbb/update_passwd.c	2023-01-05 16:29:10.000000000 +0100
+++ b/libbb/update_passwd.c	2026-04-17 09:08:19.642834814 +0200
@@ -170,8 +170,7 @@
 	lock.l_whence = SEEK_SET;
 	lock.l_start = 0;
 	lock.l_len = 0;
-	if (fcntl(old_fd, F_SETLK, &lock) < 0)
-		bb_perror_msg("warning: can't lock '%s'", filename);
+	fcntl(old_fd, F_SETLK, &lock); /* Ignore lock errors - JFFS2 does not support locking */
 	lock.l_type = F_UNLCK;
 
 	/* Read current password file, write updated /etc/passwd+ */
